@Node InterSaveExec "Creates an executable module"


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Creates an executable module which will use StonePlayer.Library to play
itself.

When you run the generated program, module will start playing and control
will be given back to AmigaDOS.

In order to stop music run the program again or send a CTRL-C to executable
module task.
@EndNode


@node Devel "Developer area"


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


This section is reserved for programmers wishing to use StoneTracker modules
in their applications.

To do so, you have four options :

	- Using 'StonePlayer.Library' shared library.

	  In order to use it, refer to files "StonePlayer.Doc" or
          "StonePlayer.Guide". Example of usage with Assembler is
	  provided in this documentation. Example of usage with 'C'
	  is provided as file 'CPlay.C'.

	- Binary file 'StonePlayer_Sys.Bin' contains an independant player
	  programmed to run in multitasking, fully compliant to OS rules.
	  To use it in Assembler, one just has to do an 'incbin'. Functions
	  are called using offsets from start of file defined in file
	  'StonePlayer/StonePlayer_Bin.I'. To use it in 'C', use usual
	  StonePlayer library includes (except for the pragmas :) and link
	  your code with linked library 'StonePlayer.lib' which contains the
	  player plus all necessary interface code to 'C' compilers.
	  For both cases, operation is the same as the library.

	  Example of usage with Assembler is provided in this documentation.
	  Example of usage with 'C' is provided as file 'CPlayBin.C'.

	- Binary file 'StonePlayer_Hard.Bin' contains an independant
	  player programmed to run with no operating system running.
	  It can only be used in Assembler, via 'incbin' ('C' is
	  NOT a good solution for directly hitting hardware).
	  Operation is the same as the library and "system" player.

	  When installing this player, you have to pass the following
	  parameters :

		* D0.w : AttnFlags from ExecBase.
		* A0   : Pointer on 4140 free bytes of CHIP memory.
	  PAULA level 2(Soft), 7-10(Audio) and 12(CiaB) interrupts
	  are used. So, DON'T TOUCH !

	  Example of usage with Assembler is provided in this documentation.

	- If none of the three options above suits you, there is a
	  mode called 'a la carte'. That means you explain your needs
	  clearly on paper and sends them to the player @{"author" link Auth}.

	  All requests will be seriously considered (provided that you
	  have bought the StoneTracker, of course...).

A 'light' version playing four tracks only for intros is being developed,
as is a version enabling to play sound fx over the music, for games.

All functions in library and binary players are designed to work with 'C'
and comply to registers rules wished by OS programmers. That means that
functions save all used CPU registers except D0/D1/A0/A1.

And, when calling user vector 'VectorID', ID number is passed through
D0.L and the stack for 'C' usage.

When calling a user vector, UserData is passed through A1 (and the stack)
and all registers can be modified.

Depending on the option you choose, refer to one of the following examples.
@{"Example with StonePlayer.Library  ", link PrgExampleLib}
@{"Example with StonePlayer_Sys.Bin  ", link PrgExampleSys}
@{"Example with StonePlayer_Hard.Bin ", link PrgExampleHard}



			@{u} StoneTracker trailer @{uu}

If you wish, you can integrate at the start of your application a
StoneTracker trailer. This trailer can be one of the provided
examples, or one that you will create personally.

Both trailers are given in binary form, under 'system' and 'hardware'
versions. Clouds trailer only works on AGA machines. StonePicture
trailer works on both AGA machines and anything that displays 256 colors
in system screens.

	- 'System' trailers can only be used with Assembler and need a single
          input parameter : you only have to pass in A0 the address of
	  'system' binary player. The trailer itself only has to
	  be INCBINned and ran by jumping to the first byte.

	- 'Hardware' trailers are different.
	  They can only be used in Assembler. They also have to be
	  INCBINned and started by jumping to their first byte.

	  Parameters to pass are as following :

	  A0 : Pointer to 'hardware' binary player
	  A1 : Pointer to some free chipram
	  A2 : Copy of VBR
	  D0 : Copy of AttnFlags from ExecBase

	  Size of chip memory passed through A1 depends on the trailer :

		- Clouds_Hard.Bin requires 414078 free bytes
		- StonePicture_Hard.Bin requires 183228 free bytes

Players (whose pointers are passed in A0 for Assembler usage) don't have to
be installed (it's not necessary to call InstallPlayer). In addition, if when
the trailer tries to install the player something goes wrong, it will exit
automatically.
@endnode

@node PrgExampleLib "Example program"


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


@{u}	Example of library usage in Assembler.	@{uu}

*****************************************
*	StonePlayer library example	*
*****************************************

************
* Includes *
************

	Include	'Exec/Exec_Lib.I'
	Include	'Dos/Dos.I'
	Include	'StonePlayer/StonePlayer.I'
	Include	'StonePlayer/StonePlayer_Lib.I'


********
* Code *
********

Start:	move.l	4.w,a6
	sub.l	a1,a1
	jsr	_LVOFindTask(a6)
	move.l	d0,a4

	lea.l	StonePlayerName(pc),a1
	moveq	#39,d0
	jsr	_LVOOpenLibrary(a6)
	tst.l	d0
	beq.s	.NoLib

	move.l	d0,a5
	lea.l	(a5),a6
	jsr	_LVOspInstallPlayer(a6)	* Installs player
	tst.l	d0			* Bye if player can't install itself
	bne.s	.CloseLib

	lea.l	Modules(pc),a0		* Installs module into player
	lea.l	Samples,a1
	sub.l	a2,a2
	jsr	_LVOspInstallModule(a6)

	link	a3,#-VL_Size
	move.l	a4,VL_UserData(sp)	* VL_UserData is used here
					* for passing Task structure
	clr.l	VL_ID(sp)
	lea.l	SongEnd(pc),a0
	move.l	a0,VL_SongEnd(sp)	* Vector called when song ends
					* or when current song number changes
	clr.l	VL_EndFadeVolSong(sp)
	clr.l	VL_EndFadeBalance(sp)
	lea.l	(sp),a0
	jsr	_LVOspSetVectors(a6)
	unlk	a3

	jsr	_LVOspStartPlayer(a6)	* Starts player

	move.l	#SIGBREAKF_CTRL_C,d0
	move.l	4.w,a6
	jsr	_LVOWait(a6)

	lea.l	(a5),a6
	moveq	#VOF_CUTDMA,d0
	jsr	_LVOspStopPlayer(a6)	* Cuts player audio outputs

	jsr	_LVOspRemovePlayer(a6)	* Removes player/frees audio channels

.CloseLib:
	lea.l	(a5),a1
	move.l	4.w,a6
	jsr	_LVOCloseLibrary(a6)

.NoLib:	moveq	#0,d0
	rts

SongEnd:	* A1 keeps Task structure
	move.l	#SIGBREAKF_CTRL_C,d0
	move.l	4.w,a6
	jmp	_LVOSignal(a6)

StonePlayerName:
	dc.b	'stoneplayer.library',0
	CNOP	0,4

Modules:
	incbin	'Ram:SPM.Rave Part II'


*	Even if, here, samples are in ChipRam , all players are able
*	to play samples from FastRam. Remove the following section
*	directive if you don't believe it !

	Section	SamplesMem,DATA_C
Samples:
	incbin	'Ram:SPS.Rave Part II'

@endnode

@node PrgExampleSys "Example program"


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


@{u}	Example of usage with StonePlayer system binary player.	@{uu}

*****************************************
*	StonePlayer Binary example	*
*****************************************

************
* Includes *
************

	Include	'Exec/Exec_Lib.I'
	Include	'Dos/Dos.I'
	Include	'StonePlayer/StonePlayer.I'
	Include	'StonePlayer/StonePlayer_Bin.I'


********
* Code *
********

Start:	move.l	4.w,a6
	sub.l	a1,a1
	jsr	_LVOFindTask(a6)
	move.l	d0,a4

	lea.l	StonePlayer(pc),a5

	jsr	spInstallPlayer(a5)	* Installs player
	tst.l	d0			* Bye if player can't install itself
	bne.s	.NoPlay

	lea.l	Modules(pc),a0		* Installs module into player
	lea.l	Samples,a1
	sub.l	a2,a2
	jsr	spInstallModule(a5)

	link	a3,#-VL_Size
	move.l	a4,VL_UserData(sp)	* VL_UserData is used here
					* for passing Task structure
	clr.l	VL_ID(sp)
	lea.l	SongEnd(pc),a0
	move.l	a0,VL_SongEnd(sp)	* Vector called when song ends
					* or when current song number changes
	clr.l	VL_EndFadeVolSong(sp)
	clr.l	VL_EndFadeBalance(sp)
	lea.l	(sp),a0
	jsr	spSetVectors(a5)
	unlk	a3

	jsr	spStartPlayer(a5)	* Starts player

	move.l	#SIGBREAKF_CTRL_C,d0
	jsr	_LVOWait(a6)

	moveq	#VOF_CUTDMA,d0
	jsr	spStopPlayer(a5)	* Cuts player audio outputs

	jsr	spRemovePlayer(a5)	* Removes player/frees audio channels

.NoPlay:
	moveq	#0,d0
	rts

SongEnd:	* A1 keeps Task structure
	move.l	#SIGBREAKF_CTRL_C,d0
	move.l	4.w,a6
	jmp	_LVOSignal(a6)

Modules:
	incbin	'Ram:SPM.Rave Part II'

StonePlayer:
	Incbin	'StonePlayer/Binary/StonePlayer_Sys.Bin'


*	Even if, here, samples are in ChipRam , all players are able
*	to play samples from FastRam. Remove the following section
*	directive if you don't believe it !

	Section	SamplesMem,DATA_C
Samples:
	incbin	'Ram:SPS.Rave Part II'

@endnode 

@node PrgExampleHard "Example program"


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


@{u}	Example of usage with StonePlayer hardware binary player.	@{uu}

*****************************************
*	StonePlayer Binary example	*
*****************************************

************
* Includes *
************

	Include	'Exec/ExecBase.I'
	Include	'Exec/Memory.I'
	Include	'Exec/Exec_Lib.I'
	Include	'Hardware/Custom.I'
	Include	'StonePlayer/StonePlayer.I'
	Include	'StonePlayer/StonePlayer_Bin.I'


*************
* Structure *
*************

	RSRESET
;---------------------
ST_ChipMem		RS.L	1
ST_VBR			RS.L	1
ST_CPU			RS.W	1
ST_INTENA		RS.W	1
ST_Quit			RS.B	1
ST_Pad			RS.B	3
ST_Size		RS.W	0


********
* Code *
********

Start:	move.l	4.w,a6

	lea.l	ReadVBR(pc),a5
	jsr	_LVOSupervisor(a6)

	lea.l	Data(pc),a5
	move.l	a0,ST_VBR(a5)
	move.w	AttnFlags(a6),ST_CPU(a5)

	move.l	#4140,d0
	move.l	#MEMF_CHIP,d1
	jsr	_LVOAllocMem(a6)
	tst.l	d0
	beq.s	.NoChipMem
	move.l	d0,ST_ChipMem(a5)

	jsr	_LVODisable(a6)
	lea.l	$DFF000,a6
	move.w	intenar(a6),d0
	move.w	#$7FFF,intena(a6)
	or.w	#$8000,d0
	move.w	d0,ST_INTENA(a5)

	bsr	DoPlayer

	lea.l	$DFF000,a6
	move.w	#$7FFF,intena(a6)
	move.w	ST_INTENA(a5),d0
	move.w	d0,intena(a6)

	move.l	4.w,a6
	jsr	_LVOEnable(a6)

	move.l	ST_ChipMem(a5),a1
	move.l	#4140,d0
	jsr	_LVOFreeMem(a6)

.NoChipMem:
	moveq.l	#0,d0
	rts

ReadVBR:
	movec	VBR,a0
	rte

Data:	dcb.b	ST_Size


DoPlayer:
	lea.l	StonePlayer(pc),a4
	move.l	ST_ChipMem(a5),a0
	move.l	ST_VBR(a5),a1
	move.w	ST_CPU(a5),d0
	jsr	spInstallPlayer(a4)	* Installs player

	lea.l	Modules(pc),a0		* Installs module into player
	lea.l	Samples,a1
	sub.l	a2,a2
	jsr	spInstallModule(a4)

	link	a3,#-VL_Size
	move.l	a5,VL_UserData(sp)	* VL_UserData is used here to
					* pass variables
	clr.l	VL_ID(sp)
	lea.l	SongEnd(pc),a0
	move.l	a0,VL_SongEnd(sp)	* Vector called when song ends
					* or when current song number changes
	clr.l	VL_EndFadeVolSong(sp)
	clr.l	VL_EndFadeBalance(sp)
	lea.l	(sp),a0
	jsr	spSetVectors(a4)
	unlk	a3

	clr.b	ST_Quit(a5)

	jsr	spStartPlayer(a4)	* Starts player

.WaitSongEnd:
	tst.b	ST_Quit(a5)
	beq.s	.WaitSongEnd

	moveq	#VOF_CUTDMA,d0
	jsr	spStopPlayer(a4)	* Cuts player audio outputs

	jmp	spRemovePlayer(a4)	* Removes player/frees audio channels

SongEnd:	* A1 keeps variables
	st	ST_Quit(a1)
	rts

Modules:
	incbin	'Ram:SPM.Rave Part II'

StonePlayer:
	Incbin	'StonePlayer/Binary/StonePlayer_Hard.Bin'


*	Even if, here, samples are in ChipRam , all players are able
*	to play samples from FastRam. Remove the following section
*	directive if you don't believe it !

	Section	SamplesMem,DATA_C
Samples:
	incbin	'Ram:SPS.Rave Part II'

@endnode

@Node "InterEditPos" "Position Editor"
@font topaz.font 8


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Opens position editor.

			Position editor
		@{" 1 " Link "PosEditTrack"}@{" 2 " Link "PosEditTrack"}@{" 3 " Link "PosEditTrack"}@{" 4 " Link "PosEditTrack"}@{" 5 " Link "PosEditTrack"}@{" 6 " Link "PosEditTrack"}@{" 7 " Link "PosEditTrack"}@{" 8 " Link "PosEditTrack"}@{"FX" Link "PosEditTrack"}
		@{"  Ins  " Link PosEditIns}@{"  Rem  " Link PosEditRem}@{"   Copy  " Link PosEditCopy}@{"  Rept  " Link PosEditRept}
		@{"  Exg  " Link PosEditExg}@{"  Sprd " Link PosEditSprd}@{"   Dub   " Link PosEditDub}@{"  Swap  " Link PosEditSwap}

@endnode

@node PosEditTrack "Track selection"


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


These buttons select which tracks will react to commands below them.
Buttons which are recessed (brighter) show tracks which are SELECTED.
@endnode

@node PosEditIns ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Inserts a position between current one and next one.
Inserted position will contain patterns numbers set to 0.
@endnode

@node PosEditRem ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Removes current position (the ones following are shifted one
position back).
@endnode

@node PosEditCopy ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Copies current position to another one which is selected by requester.
@endnode

@node PosEditRept ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Copies current position on each position between a starting and an ending one
both selected by requesters.
@endnode

@node PosEditExg ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Swaps current position with one selected by requester.
@endnode

@node PosEditSprd ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Fills pattern numbers from current position to a position selected
by requester with pattern numbers ranging from and to pattern
numbers selected by requester. This applies only to selected
tracks. Ehm.. Well.. try it!
@endnode

@node PosEditDub ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Provided that two tracks are selected, this function copies pattern
numbers from the first track to the second, from current position
to a position selected by requester.
@endnode

@node PosEditSwap ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Provided that two tracks are selected, this function swaps pattern
numbers between the first track and the second, from current position
to a position selected by requester.
@endnode

@Node InterEditPatt "Pattern editor"
@font topaz.font 8


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Opens pattern editor.

			Pattern editor
		@{" Cut " Link PatEditCut}@{"Copy " Link PatEditCopy}@{"Paste" Link PatEditPaste}@{"Swap " Link PatEditSwap}
		@{" Exg " Link PatEditExg}@{"Rem  " Link PatEditRem}@{" Ins " Link PatEditIns}@{" Del " Link PatEditDel}
		@{"OctUp" Link PatEditOctUp}@{"OctDn" Link PatEditOctDw}@{"NotUp" Link PatEditNotUp}@{"NotDn" Link PatEditNotDw}
@EndNode

@node PatEditCut ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Copies pattern under cursor into the clipboard then clears the pattern.
@endnode

@node PatEditCopy ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Copies pattern under cursor into the clipboard.
@endnode

@node PatEditPaste ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Copies pattern in clipboard over pattern under cursor.
@endnode

@node PatEditSwap ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Swaps pattern in clipboard with pattern under cursor.
@endnode

@node PatEditExg ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Swaps pattern under cursor with a pattern selected by requester.
@endnode

@node PatEditRem ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Removes patterns from pattern under cursor to the end of the list.
@endnode

@node PatEditIns ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Inserts an empty line under cursor, shifting all lines below one
line down.
@endnode

@node PatEditDel ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}



Removes a line under cursor, shifting all lines below one line up.
@endnode

@node PatEditOctUp ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Increases by one range all notes of pattern under cursor.
@endnode

@node PatEditOctDw ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Decreases by one range all notes of pattern under cursor.
@endnode

@node PatEditNotUp ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Increases by one halftone all notes of pattern under cursor.
@endnode

@node PatEditNotDw ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Decreases by one halftone all notes of pattern under cursor.
@endnode

@Node InterEditSong "Song Editor"
@font topaz.font 8


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Opens song editor.

			Song editor
		@{" Insert " Link SongEditInsert}@{" Remove " Link SongEditRemove}@{" Copy   " Link SongEditCopy}
		@{" Exchg  " Link SongEditExchg}@{" Join   " Link SongEditJoin}@{" Split  " Link SongEditSplit}
		@{" Single " Link SongEditSingle}@{" Print  " Link SongEditPrint}@{" PrtAll " Link SongEditPrtAll}
@EndNode

@node SongEditInsert ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Creates a new song after having requested some parameters, then inserts
it at current song number, shifting all following songs by one number.
@endnode

@node SongEditRemove ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Removes current song, shifting all following songs by one number.
@endnode

@node SongEditCopy ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Copies current song over a song selected by requester.
@endnode

@node SongEditExchg ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Swaps current song with a song selected by requester.
@endnode

@node SongEditJoin ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Adds positions of a song selected by requester next to the positions of
current song.
@endnode

@node SongEditSplit ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Splits current song in two, by moving its positions from current to
end into another song selected by requester.
@endnode

@node SongEditSingle ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


After you confirmed, removes all songs but the current one.
@endnode

@node SongEditPrint ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Prints current song.
@endnode

@node SongEditPrtAll ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Prints all songs.
@endnode

