@EndNode

@node CnfPackMode ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


StoneTracker features samples bank packing in order to spare some space on
(hard)disk, drawback being a longer load/save time. As of version 1.26, four
options are available :

 . None

   Samples are saved in their original state without being packed. Use this
   option if you can't stand packing/depacking time or if the module is going
   to be used in an application of yours (in this case, samples MUST be
   unpacked !!).

   (Note that when using 'update' function that saves modifications, if you
    haven't changed the samples, then the bank will not be re-saved, avoiding
    possible packing time.)

 . DeltaHuffman 

   The fastest packer/depacker and the least efficient.
   Pack ratio : 20-25% average.
   Author : Emmanuel Marty

 . CrM / LZH-Delta

   Method that packs the most and which is the slowest.
   Pack ratio : 35-40% average.
   Author : Thomas Schwartz, programmer of CrunchMania.

   ( Note that this method requires CrM.Library shared library in LIBS: for
     packing - StoneTracker unpacks by itself. We are not granted to
     distribute this file along with StoneTracker. )

 . StoneCruncher / Mickey

   Intermediate method between DeltaHuffman and CrM/LZH-Delta.
   Pack ratio : 25-30% average.
   Author : Michael Lavaire

   ( This method requires StoneCruncher.Library shared library - provided -
     in LIBS: for both packing and unpacking )
@endnode

@node CnfOpenTrk ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Default number of tracks that will show the song which is created at
program startup time (ranging from 4 to 8).
@endnode

@node CnfOpenFXChn ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Defines if song created at program startup time will immediatly show a FX
track or not.
@endnode

@node CnfMaxOpenTrk ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Maximum tracks available on the song created at program startup time
(ranging from 4 to 8).
@endnode

@node CnfNewSongFXChn ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Defines if a new song created will immediatly show a FX track or not.
@endnode

@node CnfNewSongTrk ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Defines the default number of tracks that will be displayed in new song
creation request.
@endnode

@node CnfBreakOnNull ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Defines if sound must be muted when player meets a nullspeed command (@{"0F00" link "Set Speed"}),
if not player will stop playing ;) the music and will let current notes end.
@endnode

@node CnfDefKHz ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Default mixing frequency for "virtual tracks" modes (5-8 tracks). All samples
played on virtual tracks will be recomputed to this frequency. Obviously,
the greater the frequency, the greater the quality, and the slower the
machine.

On a "normal" display (PAL or NTSC), that means which displays at an
horizontal frequency of 15.75 Khz, mixing frequency ranges from 4 to 28 Khz.
If you own a (S)VGA, Multisync, etc. display which displays "deinterlaced"
modes of ECS and AGA at an horizontal frequency of 31.5 Khz, mixing
frequency will range from 4 to 50 Khz (Amiga works the way it works...)
@endnode

@node CnfAllocTreshold ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


StoneTracker handles up to 65.536 patterns, and, contrary to ProTracker
(which has a maximum of 64), it can't allocate required memory for
this maximum number of patterns once at program startup time (for
65.536 patterns, one would need 64 Megabytes of workspace [and which
cannot be put as virtual memory on harddisk] !!).. So StoneTracker
allocates memory as required. In order to avoid memory fragmentation,
patterns memory is not allocated seperately for each pattern but
by groups.

This number defines the number of patterns reserved in one allocation.
The greater the number, the smaller the chances of fragmentation,
and the greater the chances of spilling memory (for example, if
the Tracker is told to allocate patterns 100 per 100 and you have
101 patterns in memory, there will be memory allocated for 200
patterns).

In most cases you won't even have to care about this parameter,
as its default value of 64 seems efficient (we are using it
from the start of StoneTracker development).
@endnode

@node CnfEnableKeyRepeat ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Defines if keyboard repeat is enabled in "pattern edition" mode and in
"record" mode (leaving the key pressed repeats the same note).
@endnode

@node CnfSaveIFFSamples ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Defines if StoneTracker will save samples as IFF when using command
for saving seperated samples ('Save Samp'). If not, samples will be
saved as RAW format (no header).
@endnode

@node CnfOpenPattLen ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Length of patterns (in lines) shown at program startup. Ranges from $1 to
$FFF.
@endnode

@node CnfAction ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Defines which action is concerned by default parameters below (number of
auto-created @{"patterns" link CnfAddPatt}, @{"control patterns" link CnfAddFxPatt} and @{"positions" link CnfAllocPosition}) when program
starts, or when a new song is created (these parameters being then
default parameters shown in request).
@endnode

@node CnfConfirmOverwrite ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Defines if StoneTracker will ask before writing over a file that already
exists.
@endnode

@node CnfMaxPattLen ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Maximum length of patterns (in number of lines), ranging from $1 to $FFF.
Really tune this number function of your needs! The greater this number,
the greater the required workspace (under editor, only).
@endnode

@node CnfAddPatt ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Number of patterns automatically created either when program starts or when a
new song is created (see @{"Action" link CnfAction}) (in the latter case this is the default
value shown in song creation request).
@endnode

@node CnfAskForAREXX ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Defines if StoneTracker will warn you when, at startup time, it states that
RexxMaster is not running and so no AREXX command will be able to run.
@endnode

@node CnfWarnPatAbove ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


When adding patterns by typing directly a pattern number (that doesn't exist)
into the slots above tracks, any addition of a number of patterns greater
than this number will require confirmation.
@endnode

@node CnfAddFXPatt ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Number of control patterns automatically created either when program starts
or when a new song is created (see @{"Action" link CnfAction}) (in the latter case this is
the default value shown in song creation request).
@endnode

@node CnfKeepAppIconPos ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Defines if StoneTracker should use the position on Workbench screen
stored in icon file used as AppIcon, if not it will make it "float"
(Workbench will position the icon where possible)
@endnode

@node CnfWarnPosAbove ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


When adding positions by typing directly a position number (that doesn't
exist) into the position number above line numbers, any addition of a number
of positions greater than this number will require confirmation.
@endnode

@node CnfAllocPosition ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Number of positions automatically created either when program starts or when
a new song is created (see @{"Action" link CnfAction}) (in the latter case this is the
default value shown in song creation request).
@endnode

@node CnfAutoCloseWorkbench ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Defines if StoneTracker should try to close the Workbench when it starts up,
in order to free some chip memory.
@endnode

@node CnfFullLockInInactive ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Defines if StoneTracker screen must be locked (nothing is refreshed) when it
isn't displayed, because you are multitasking on another application - this
enables to free a lot of CPU time. If this option is disabled, StoneTracker
will only lower its task priority, making it less greedy for CPU time,
giving it back to the other running tasks.
@endnode

@node CnfNum ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Palette number. You can define up to four different palettes for StoneTracker
screen and change instantly, depending on your mood, using this button.
@endnode

@node CnfSlider1 ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Scrolls list of colors available on the left.
@endnode

@node CnfSlider2 ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Scrolls list of StoneTracker screen regions available on the left.
@endnode

@node CnfSliderColor1 ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Lets you choose the level of intensity of red, green and blue for currently
edited color.
@endnode

@node CnfNumMeter ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Number of vu-meters palette. You can define up to four different palettes
for vu-meters (ChannelMeters) and change instantly, depending on your
mood, using this button.
@endnode

@node CnfSliderColor2 ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Lets you choose the level of intensity of red, green and blue for currently
edited vu-meter line.
@endnode

@node CnfSlider3 ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Selects the line of vu-meter where the color must be edited.
@endnode

@node CnfMeterType ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Selects the default vu-meter type used at program startup, that means "real"
(average sound volume of what is currently played by the corresponding
track - like ProTracker 3.xx), "volume" (volume of last sample played on
the track), "frequency" (note height of last played sample) and "fake"
(volume set to maximum when a sample starts, then smoothly growing down -
just like the very first trackers)
@endnode

@node CnfSave ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Saves configuration so that it will be restored next time your start the
program. Configuration is saved as "ENVARC:StoneTracker.prefs"
@endnode

@node CnfUse ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Returns to the Tracker with current configuration, but doesn't save it - next
time your run StoneTracker, configuration will be as it was before running
configuration editor.
@endnode

@node CnfCancel ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Cancels modifications made to the configuration and returns to the Tracker
with config as it was before entering the configuration editor.
@endnode

@node CnfC ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Copies a color from a vu-meter line to another. Method : select line to be
copied, press this button once, select the target line, press this button
again.
@endnode

@node CnfS ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Spread colors between two vu-meter lines. Method : select starting line, press
this button once, select ending line, press this button again
@endnode

@node CnfDosPaths "Default paths configuration window"
@font topaz.font 8


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Opens default paths configuration window.

	  DOS Paths...
	-------------------------------------------
	|  Module Path : @{"ST-00:               ",Link CnfModulePath}@{"G", Link CnfModulePathFile} |
	|  Sample Path : @{"RAM:                 ",Link CnfSamplePath}@{"G", Link CnfSamplePathFile} |
	| Default Path : @{"RAM:                 ",Link CnfDefaultPath}@{"G", Link CnfDefaultPathFile} |
	|-----------------------------------------|
	|  Module Mask : @{"~(SPS|SMPL)~(???|????).",Link CnfModuleMask} |
	|  Sample Mask : @{"#?                     ",Link CnfSampleMask} |
	|-----------------------------------------|
	| Printer Path : @{"PRT:                   ",Link CnfPrinterPath} |
	|  Page Height : @{"64      ",Link CnfPageHeight}@{"  Fetch ...   ",Link CnfFetch} |
	-------------------------------------------
@endnode

@node CnfModulePath ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Default path where StoneTracker will fetch modules when using module load
and save commands. If you are working with a harddisk, setting here where
your modules are located will avoid indicating it all the time.

NOTE: if you change this path, the new one will be taken into account only
      when you restart the program.
@endnode

@node CnfModulePathFile ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Selects the @{"default modules path" link CnfModulePath} by file request.
@endnode

@node CnfSamplePath ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Default path where StoneTracker will fetch samples when using sample and
samplebank load and save commands. If you are working with a harddisk,
setting here where your samples are located will avoid indicating it all
the time.

NOTE: if you change this path, the new one will be taken into account only
      when you restart the program.
@endnode

@node CnfSamplePathFile ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Selects the @{"default samples path" link CnfSamplePath} by file request.
@endnode

@node CnfDefaultPath ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Default path for all file commands that do not handle a particular file
type, mainly 'delete file' command.
@endnode

@node CnfDefaultPathFile ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Selects the @{"default misc files path" link CnfDefaultPath} by file request.
@endnode

@node CnfModuleMask ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Default "Mask" used in module file requests. This mask enables to include or
exclude files having particular letters or words in their name. The main
goal here is to exclude samplebank files, beginning by "SPS.".
@endnode

@node CnfSampleMask ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Default "Mask" used in sample file requests. This mask enables to include or
exclude files having particular letters or words in their name.
@endnode

@node CnfPrinterPath ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Path used by AmigaDOS for accessing printer, normally "PRT:".
@endnode

@node CnfPageHeight ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Number of lines per page of your printer.
@endnode

@node CnfFetch ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Fetches the number of lines per page of your printer in your prefs files.
@endnode

@node CnfAREXXMacros "Opens AREXX macros installation window"
@font topaz.font 8


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Opens AREXX macros installation window.

	  AREXX Macros ...
	--------------------------------
	| @{"A:                    ",Link CnfAREXXMacro} |@{" ", Link CnfSliderMacro}| |
	| @{"B:                    ",Link CnfAREXXMacro} |  | |
	| @{"C:                    ",Link CnfAREXXMacro} |@{"^", Link CnfSliderMacro}| |
	| @{"D:                    ",Link CnfAREXXMacro} |@{"v", Link CnfSliderMacro}| |
	|------------------------------|
	| @{"                          ",Link CnfAREXXMacroString}@{"G", Link CnfSliderMacroFile}|
	--------------------------------
@endnode

@node CnfAREXXMacro ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


AREXX macros list. 14 can be installed in the same time, corresponding to
letters A to N (their @{"keyboard shortcut" link Keyboard} being CTRL + their letter).
@endnode

@node CnfSliderMacro ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Scrolls AREXX macros list.
@endnode

@node CnfAREXXMacroString ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Lets you edit the name of the file containing the AREXX macro to be installed
on the letter currently selected in the list above.
@endnode

@node CnfSliderMacroFile ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Selects by file request the file containing the AREXX macro to be installed
on the letter currently selected in the list above.
@endnode

@node CnfMiscParameters "Opens misc parameters configuration window"
@font topaz.font 8


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Opens misc parameters configuration window.

	  Misc parameters ...
	----------------------------------------
	|   App Icon: @{"StoneTracker.Info    ",Link CnfAppIcon}@{"G", Link CnfGetAppFile} |
	|  AREXX I/O: @{"CON:0/0//100/StoneREXX/",Link CnfAREXXIO} |
	|     Hotkey: @{"control alt s          ",Link CnfHotKey} |
	| ScreenMode: @{"PAL:High Res         ",Link CnfScreenMode}@{"G", Link CnfGetScreenMode} |
	|--------------------------------------|
	| Fast load : @{"@| SampleSize ",Link CnfFastLoad} KB @{"256 ", link CnfFastLoadSize} |
	----------------------------------------
@endnode

@node CnfAppIcon ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Name of icon file containing AppIcon to be used for StoneTracker.
@endnode

@node CnfGetAppFile ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Selects by file request the icon file containing AppIcon to be used for
StoneTracker.
@endnode

@node CnfAREXXIO ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Defines console window to be used for i/o of AREXX commands ran from the
StoneTracker.
@endnode

@node CnfHotKey ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


StoneTracker "Hot Key". The indicated key sequence when pressed makes
editor screen either come to front or open if it was "hidden".
@endnode

@node CnfScreenMode ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Shows screen mode for StoneTracker screen (and configuration screen).
@endnode

@node CnfGetScreenMode ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


Selects screen mode for StoneTracker screen (and configuration screen) using
a request. Note that StoneTracker screen requires at least a size of 672 per
200 pixels, and that you will need a height of 256 pixels to work properly.
@endnode

@node CnfFastLoad ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


StoneTracker features fast memory samples loading, if you don't have enough
chip memory. This option will slightly slow down the player in 4-tracks mode,
and may speed it up in virtual tracks modes (5-8 tracks).

This button rules the condition of loading samples in fast memory rather than
in chip. Three options :

	- never

	- if sample size is greater than a @{"given size" link CnfFastLoadSize}

	- if free chip memory size falls under a @{"given size" link CnfFastLoadSize}.
@endnode

@node CnfFastLoadSize ""


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


StoneTracker features fast memory samples loading, if you don't have enough
chip memory. This option will slightly slow down the player in 4-tracks mode,
and may speed it up in virtual tracks modes (5-8 tracks).

Defines in kbytes either the minimum size for a sample to be loaded in fastram,
or the minimum size of free chip memory under which samples are loaded in
fastram, depending on current @{"mode" link CnfFastLoad}.
@endnode

@node Keyboard "Keyboard shortcuts ..."


			@{fg Highlight}StoneTracker V1.26@{fg text}


			@{u}Keyboard shortcuts@{uu}


@{u}General keys :@{uu}

General keys :

F1	      Select octaves #1 and #2
F2	      Select octaves #2 and #3
SHIFT F3      Cut pattern
SHIFT F4      Copy pattern
SHIFT F5      Paste pattern
CTRL F3       Cut effects
CTRL F4       Copy effects
CTRL F5       Paste effects
F6 TO F10     Move into the pattern (for compatibility with other trackers)
SHIFT F6-F10  Record pattern position on corresponding key
              (F6-F10 without qualifier will bring you back here)
AMIGA F6-F10  Clears stored position on corresponding key
              (warps back to native mode)
ALT F6-F10    Plays from pattern position recorded on corresp. key
CTRL F6-F10   Records from pattern position recorded on corresp. key
SPACE         Stop music, enter/exit edit mode.
DEL           Delete note under cursor (edit mode only)
ALT DEL       Clears effects of track under cursor
SHIFT DEL     Clears note of track under cursor
CTRL DEL      Clears whole pattern
BACKSPACE     Delete line under cursor (edit mode only)
SHIFT BACKSP. Insert new line under cursor (edit mode only)
RIGHT SHIFT   Start recording        \
RIGHT AMIGA   Play current position  /  with left shift (or right mousebutton)
RIGHT ALT     Play current song     /   starts at current line
BOTH ALTs     Restart and play current song
<             Cut current voice
`             Pick song by requester
RETURN	      Enter step mode, step one (with left shift: exit step mode)
UP            Move one line up
SHIFT-UP      Move 16 lines up
ALT-UP        Move to first line
CTRL-UP       Move to previous position
DOWN          Move one line down
SHIFT-DOWN    Move 16 lines down
ALT-DOWN      Move to last line
CTRL-DOWN     Move to next position
LEFT	      Move one character left
SHIFT-LEFT    Move one voice left
ALT-LEFT      Move to first voice
CTRL-LEFT     Show previous command column (multieffects)
RIGHT	      Move one character right
SHIFT-RIGHT   Move one voice right
ALT-RIGHT     Move to last voice
CTRL-RIGHT    Show next command column (multieffects)
TAB	      Move to the note on next voice to the right

@{u}Effects editing keys :@{uu}

SHIFT 0-9     Stores effect displayed by current track on corresp. key
ALT 0-9       Writes effect stored on corresp. key under the cursor
              (default effects are ProTracker's)
ALT "\"       Copies effects above cursor under cursor
ALT "="       Copies effects above cursor under cursor and adds 1 to
              the parameter
ALT "-"       Copies effects above cursor under cursor and substracts
              1 from the parameter

@{u}Notes keyboard (just like other trackers) :@{uu}

 23 567 90 -		 23 567 90 -
AZERTYUIOP^$		QWERTYUIOP{}
 SD GHJ LM		 SD GHJ L;
WXCVBN,;:=		ZXCVBNM,./

@{u}Numeric keypad :@{uu}

without qualifiers - set lower digit of sample number

[]/*	: x1,x2,x3,x4
789-	: x5,x6,x7,x8
456+	: x9,xA,xB,xC
123	: xD,xE,xF
.	: x0
0 	: select sample 0
ENTER   : pick sample by requester

with left shift - set higher digit of sample number

[]/*	: 1x,2x,3x,4x
789-	: 5x,6x,7x,8x
456+	: 9x,Ax,Bx,Cx
123	: Dx,Ex,Fx
.	: 0x
0 	: select sample 0
ENTER   : pick sample by requester

@{u}Note Skip keys :@{uu}

CTRL + 1-9	Select new Note Skip value.

@{u}Requester keys :@{uu}

ESC		\
N		Negative answer
Amiga/B		/

Y		\ Positive answer
Amiga/V         /

RETURN          Satisfy single-answer requester (ex. Info)
                Select an element in a list (ex. Pick Sample)

UP/DOWN keys	If the requester shows a list of elements, go up or down
                in that list (16 times faster with SHIFT, directly at top
                or bottom with ALT)

@{u}AREXX Macro calls (with ctrl) :@{uu}

A-N		Call AREXX Macro A-N

@{u}Shortcuts (with left shift) :@{uu}

O		Load Module
W		Save Module
L		Load Sample
M		Save Sample
B		Save Bank
U		Update
D		Delete File(s)
R		Remap patterns
C		Clear patterns
V		Clear positions
G		Clear songs
A		Add song
T		Time song
X		Mix position to sample
F		Flush samples
E		Edit commands
S		Open/Close Sample Editor
`		Pick pattern by requester
\		Close/Open Workbench
N		Make editor inactive
H		Hide
I		Information
Q		Quit
@EndNode
